Citation.sTitle: Vapor Pressures of Aluminum Tribromide and Aluminum Triiodide and Their Standard Sublimation Enthalpies
Citation.sAbstract: Total vapor pressures of AlBr3 and AlI3 were measured by a torsion effusion apparatus. Their temperature dependences are expressed by the equations log(p/Pa) = (14.78 +- 0.60) - (4700 +- 200)/(T/K) from (301.0 to 351.0) K and log(p/Pa) = (15.52 +- 0.30) - (5960 +- 150)/(T/K) from (359.5 to 419.5) K for AlBr3 and AlI3, respectively. Practically, AlBr3 vaporizes in a dimeric form, while AlI3 vaporizes in monomeric and dimeric forms. Treating the vapor pressures of AlBr3 by second- and third-law methods, the standard sublimation enthalpy ?Hdeg (298 K) = (90 +- 4) kJ*mol-1 was derived. For AlI3, treating the partial pressures of monomer and dimer gaseous species, deduced from the measured total vapor pressures and the constant of dimer-monomer equilibrium reported in the literature, by second- and third-law methods, the standard enthalpies ?Hdeg (298 K) = (110 +- 4) kJ*mol-1 and ?Hdeg (298 K) = (119 +- 4) kJ*mol-1 associated to the sublimation reactions of AlI3 according to the AlI3(s) ? AlI3(g) and 2AlI3(s) ? Al2I6(g), respectively, were selected.
